-- FACTBOX: Key players in video conference industry
-- 
-- Thu Oct 1, 2009 11:40am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/10/01/us-cisco-tandberg-sb-idUSTRE5904L320091001

 

 (Reuters) - Cisco has agreed to buy Norwegian videoconferencing company Tandberg for $3 billion in cash. 

 Here is a list of some major players in the video conferencing industry: * TANDBERG: Market Capitalization - $2.6 billion (2009) Revenue - $808.8 million (2008) Headcount - 1,451 -- Delivered 66,631 end point systems in 2008 * POLYCOM: Market Capitalization - $2.2 billion (2009) Revenue - $1.1 billion (2008) Employees - 2,600 -- Video solutions generated $560.06 million in revenues of the total group revenue * RADVISION: Market Capitalization - $180.3 million (2009) Revenue - $84.75 million (2008) Employees - 442 * AVISTAR: Market Capitalization - 27.02 million (2009) Revenue - 8.76 million (2008) Employees - 50 (Writing by Carl Bagh, Bangalore Editorial Reference Unit; Editing by  David Cutler )